HEADWORD: Collaboration
<hw>Col*lab`o*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of working together; united labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the act of willingly cooperating with an enemy,
especially an enemy nation occupying one's own country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>collaborationist</ent>⟦br⟧
